00:42:21.360 --> 00:42:25.380
Like, did your work
start at a smaller scale?

00:42:25.380 --> 00:42:26.959
Yeah, just more on that.

00:42:26.959 --> 00:42:27.750
ZARIA FORMAN: Yeah.

00:42:30.420 --> 00:42:34.830
I guess my professional work
began my last year in college,

00:42:34.830 --> 00:42:36.610
and I was working
pretty big actually.

00:42:36.610 --> 00:42:42.470
I made a couple of 6-by-8-foot
pieces for my senior show.

00:42:42.470 --> 00:42:45.870
And I was drawing
really big skies--

00:42:45.870 --> 00:42:51.632
storms, hurricanes from
weather photography.

00:42:51.632 --> 00:42:53.340
So scale has always
been important to me.

00:42:53.340 --> 00:42:56.130
But especially after I got
back from that first trip

00:42:56.130 --> 00:42:58.620
to Antarctica in
the winter of 2015,

00:42:58.620 --> 00:43:01.800
I was just like, how
can I do this landscape

00:43:01.800 --> 00:43:08.520
justice without going as hugely
massive as possible, as much

00:43:08.520 --> 00:43:12.780
as I can afford and
can do in my studio?

00:43:12.780 --> 00:43:15.090
Because it's just so epic.

00:43:15.090 --> 00:43:18.390
And it's like, you can use
all these grandiose words,

00:43:18.390 --> 00:43:20.700
and it's like nothing
really describes it.

00:43:20.700 --> 00:43:23.550
And that's why I am trying
to draw them because I don't

00:43:23.550 --> 00:43:25.670
know how to put it into words.

00:43:25.670 --> 00:43:27.780
So yeah, I feel like the
scale is really important

00:43:27.780 --> 00:43:32.550
to make you feel like you're
standing in front of a glacier.

00:43:32.550 --> 00:43:33.750
You need that scale.

00:43:33.750 --> 00:43:34.590
It's so important.

00:43:34.590 --> 00:43:37.170
And so I do work--

00:43:37.170 --> 00:43:39.616
I make smaller pieces as
kind of more like studies,

00:43:39.616 --> 00:43:41.490
but also just because
they are so much easier

00:43:41.490 --> 00:43:45.270
to transport and sell.

00:43:45.270 --> 00:43:48.677
But the larger ones are
really where my heart is.

00:43:48.677 --> 00:43:50.760
